==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Blende
<hw>Blende</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G., fr.
<ets>blenden</ets> to blind, dazzle, deceive, fr. <ets>blind</ets>
blind. So called either in allusion to its dazzling luster; or
(<ets>Dana</ets>) because, though often resembling galena, it yields no
lead. Cf. <er>Sphalerite</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>A mineral, called also <altname>sphalerite</altname>, and by miners
<altname>mock lead</altname>, <altname>false galena</altname>, and
<altname>black-jack</altname>. It is a zinc sulphide, but often contains
some iron. Its color is usually yellow, brown, or black, and its luster
resinous.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A general term for some minerals,
chiefly metallic sulphides which have a somewhat brilliant but
nonmetallic luster.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>blended</ent>⟦br⟧
